I"…<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<div class="grid-2">
<div>
    <p>Use shadows to highlight differences in elevation between two components.</p>

    <p>Shadows can be applied to multiple components, including cards, menus, sidebars, and tooltips.</p>
  </div>
<div>
    <p><img src="../images/patterns/shadows/elevation-example.jpg" alt="Example of an activity stream card with the shadow style applied" /></p>

    <figcaption>A shadow applied to a card</figcaption>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 id="style">Style</h2>

<div class="grid-2">
  <div>
    <p>Based on how marked the difference needs to be, pick from three levels of elevation.</p>

    <table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Shadow</th>
      <th>X</th>
      <th>Y</th>
      <th>Blur</th>
      <th>Color</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>10</td>
      <td>0</td>
      <td>1px</td>
      <td>4px</td>
      <td><code>rgba(12, 12, 13, 0.1)</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>20</td>
      <td>0</td>
      <td>2px</td>
      <td>8px</td>
      <td><code>rgba(12, 12, 13, 0.1)</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>30</td>
      <td>0</td>
      <td>4px</td>
      <td>16px</td>
      <td><code>rgba(12, 12, 13, 0.1)</code></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
  </div>

  <p><img src="../images/patterns/shadows/elevation.svg" alt="Asset that shows the three diffent styles of elevation, from lower to higher elevation" /></p>
